On most of what you said, many of us vets agree! Your last statement is unfair, however. Many vets have never portrayed the Vietnamese as barbarians or monsters. As a matter of fact, many of us do what we can to dispell any such BULLSHIT! Although, I will not exoerate all Viet Nam veterans, there are quite of few of us on this site that have done whatever they can, and fought many battles on these threads to do such as I speak. May I point out a couple of names such as Tom Dier and John Ratliff and other, not to mention myself.<br><br>
And I have not mentioned the anti-war types and other civilians that have contributed to this site, proclaiming just those things you mentioned. <br><br>
Is there a problem with perception, yes, I believe there is. What we need to do is to be able to identify the sources that cause such misconception and deal with those. Such as the pulp publishing companies that turn out those &quot;actual&quot; historical accounts and that of the film industry.<br><br>
So, before shooting from the hip (like I have never been known to do any such thing!), I suggest you pick your targets appropriately, instead of just a shotgun approach. Read the many threads on this site and find who is friend and foe. You just might find that many of us grieve for the over six million killed.<br><br>
I look foward to your further posts as well as any other from the Vietnamese community. Speak your piece and share!
